<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-08-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName>, Acting
                                    Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Pierrepont</persName>, district attorney.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-08-04"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 4,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards
                                    Pierrepont</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States District
                                    Attorney, New York:</hi></p>
                            <p>The Acting Secretary of the Navy, at the request of this Department,
                                yesterday ordered the commandant at New York to act under your
                                directions in the matter of the Spanish gun-boats. The Juniata, the
                                Dale, the Dictator, the Frolic, and some armed tugs are ready to
                                co-operate with you.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>